Important: Make sure you are on an i686‑class CPU (Pentium Pro or newer). While the ISO is labeled i386, modern packages and kernels require i686 instructions. Attempting to run on i486/i586 will cause crashes or incompatibility.

1 Download 32-bit PC (i386) server install image Server install image https://releases.ubuntu.com/16.04/
2 On Software Selection leave it standard system utilities and enter
3 After Install run sudo nano /etc/os-release then Change
NAME="Ubuntu"
VERSION="16.04.6 LTS (Xenial Xerus)"
ID=ubuntu
ID_LIKE=debian
PRETTY_NAME="Ubuntu 16.04.6 LTS (Xenial Xerus)"
VERSION_ID="16.04"
HOME_URL="http://www.ubuntu.com/"
SUPPORT_URL"http://help.ubuntu.com/"
BUG_REPORT_URL="http://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/"
VERSION_CODENAME=xenial
UBUNTU_CODENAME=xenial

To

NAME="Syslack Linux"
VERSION="1.5"
ID=syslack
PRETTY_NAME="Syslack Linux"
VERSION_ID="1.5"
HOME_URL="https://github.com/syslacklinux/Syslack-Linux"
